<title>USA: Republic denies Laidlaw rumor.</title>
<headline>Republic denies Laidlaw rumor.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Republic Industries Inc denied Canadian market rumors that it was planning to buy the solid waste management unit of Laidlaw Inc.</p>
<p>&quot;It's not true. There is no truth to it,&quot; said Republic spokesman Ronald Castell.</p>
<p>Shares of Laidlaw rose on the Toronto Stock Exchange amid speculation that a transaction was imminent.</p>
<p>Republic stock was down 1/8 at 26-1/8.</p>
<p>Republic has been extremely active in acquisitions in recent months, most notably with its proposed purchase of ADT Ltd.</p>
<p>--Robin Sidel, 212/859-1723</p>
